  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. United States:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Currency and Foreign Transactions Reporting Act\n\n3. European Union:\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- EU Financial Intelligence Units (FIUs)\n- Comprehensive regulatory standards\n\n4. Key compliance requirements:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n5. Enforcement mechanisms:\n- Financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial sectors.",
